data.title: Nasdaq drops 350 points, Dow down 0.10% to 49,432.55, and NASDAQ down 1.57% to 22,788.62. S&P 500 falls 0.88% to 6,884.75. Initial jobless claims rise by 4,000 to 212,000.
data.description: This morning, U.S. stocks experienced mostly negative trading, with the Nasdaq Composite dropping over 350 points. The Dow traded down by 0.10% to 49,432.55, while the NASDAQ fell by 1.57% to 22,788.62. The S&P 500 also saw a decline, dropping by 0.88% to 6,884.75. Financial shares were the leading sector, gaining 1.2%, while information technology stocks fell by 2.2%. U.S. initial jobless claims increased by 4,000 from the previous week to 212,000 in the third week of February, slightly below market expectations of 215,000. Avalon Globocare Corp (NASDAQ: ALBT) shares surged by 123% to $1.14 after being accepted into the Advanced Micro Devices AI Developer Program. Antelope Enterprise Holdings Ltd (NASDAQ: AEHL) also saw a boost, with shares surging by 79%. For more details, please refer to the full story on Benzinga.com.
